50|$|Some annuities {{also have}} an {{additional}} feature called a Market Value Adjustment or MVA. MVA applies when a withdrawal is made from the annuity {{in excess of the}} penalty-free amount. Generally, <b>if</b> <b>interest</b> <b>rates</b> are lower at time of the withdrawal than at the time the policy was purchased, the value of the annuity would increase. <b>If</b> <b>interest</b> <b>rates</b> are higher, the reverse is true.|$|E
