50|$|As {{interest}} rate insurance protects the holder from rising {{interest rate}}s but does not raise their initial pay rate, <b>if</b> <b>interest</b> <b>rates</b> fall, the policyholder will see a benefit in reduced payments on their mortgage or loan when compared to a fixed rate alternative.|$|E
50|$|The {{yield of}} a bond is {{inversely}} related to its price today: {{if the price of}} a bond falls, its yield goes up. Conversely, <b>if</b> <b>interest</b> <b>rates</b> decline (the market yield declines), then the price of the bond should rise (all else being equal).|$|E
